Here's your complete Ansible RHEL patching automation suite — 20 files in a production-ready role structure.
What's Included
4 Playbooks
Playbook
Purpose
patch_all_waves.yml
Full wave-based rollout: Dev → Staging → Production
patch_security.yml
Security/CVE-targeted patches, emergency use
patch_dryrun.yml
Check what would be patched — no changes applied
patch_rollback.yml
Rollback via dnf history undo with reboot
Role Tasks (5 stages)
Stage
What Happens
Preflight
OS check, disk space, DNF lock, repo connectivity, maintenance window
Pre-patch
Save package list, record running services, count updates, notify Slack/email
Patch
dnf update (security/all/bugfix/advisory), kernel detection, smart reboot
Post-patch
Service health, failed units, disk/memory check, package diff, remaining CVEs
Report
HTML + text reports saved on host and fetched to controller
Key Features
Wave-based serial rollout — stops if failure threshold exceeded (max_fail_percentage)
Kernel-aware reboot — only reboots when kernel actually changed
Maintenance window enforcement — configurable time gate for production
Rollback by DNF history — undo last or specific transaction ID
Package diff logging — exact before/after package comparison
Slack & email notifications — start + completion hooks
Per-environment vars — group_vars/production.yml vs group_vars/dev.yml
